cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.DM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper deals with the Hospitals / Residents problem with Couples (HRC) which is a classic example of a matching problem in game theory. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents Integer Programming (IP) and Constraint Programming (CP) models for MIN BP HRC, which are commonly used in AI for optimization problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the complexity of the problem and presents a polynomial-time algorithm for a restricted case. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses empirical evaluation to compare the performance of the IP and CP models. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems and matching theory, which are topics in discrete mathematics.
